<Issue id="28685" key="FABCJ-79" number="79" project="11208" reporter="c0rwin" assignee="c0rwin" creator="c0rwin" type="10000" summary="Harden gradle configuration of the fabric chaincode java project" priority="3" resolution="10000" status="6" created="2018-03-20 15:53:19.0" updated="2019-11-30 21:10:24.0" resolutiondate="2018-03-21 08:30:48.0" votes="0" watches="1" workflowId="56694"> <description><! CDATA There is a need to add gradle plugins to support seamless integration with Eclipse and IntelliJ IDE's, e.g.  {code}  apply plugin 'idea'  apply plugin 'eclipse-wtp'  {code}    additionally need to extract common dependency of the child project into the parent, following  {code}  dependencies { compile 'commons-cli:commons-cli:1.4' compile 'commons-logging:commons-logging:1.2'  testCompile 'junit:junit:4.12' testCompile 'org.hamcrest:hamcrest-library:1.3' testCompile 'org.mockito:mockito-core:2.+' }  {code}    instead of being defined at shim/build.gradle, need to be extracted to build.gradle.    In order to be able to utilize the ability to deploy into local maven repository there is a need to add maven plugin support:    {code}  apply plugin: 'java'  apply plugin: 'maven'  {code}    Currently gradle configuration missing properties of supported Java source and target version  {code}  sourceCompatibility = 1.8 targetCompatibility = 1.8  {code}    The children project build.gradle file defines sourceSet while missing the main/java folder, as well using protobuf plugin, while doesn't defines placement of proto files.    {code}  sourceSets { main { java { // adding the protobuf & grpc generated source explicitly, // so that IDEs can find the generated sources. srcDirs =  'build/generated/source/proto/main/grpc', 'build/generated/source/proto/main/java', 'src/main/java'  } proto { srcDirs 'src/main/proto' } }  test { java { srcDir 'src/test' } } }  {code}  ></description> </Issue>
